# 18_palette_dropdowns — substrate-layer suite for the fill/stroke
# palette DropDowns in the toolbar swatch-picker section (s197 m2).
#
# Substrate-style test (per TESTING.md grandfather clause). Each
# sub-test proves the substrate contract holds — abbrev resolves,
# verbs dispatch, queries read back.
#
# Scope (s197 m2): the two palette DropDowns inside
# build_swatch_picker_section, one per slot:
#
#   pop_tb_fill_pdd   Fill swatch-picker palette dropdown
#   pop_tb_strk_pdd   Stroke swatch-picker palette dropdown
#
# Architectural note (the discriminator): these dropdowns are
# constructed with an EMPTY StringList model, then have their model
# swapped at runtime via dd->set_model(sl) inside
# rebuild_palette_dropdown() once the swatch library is wired. The
# pre-s197-m2 substrate stored Glib::RefPtr<Gtk::StringList> m_model
# at construction and walked THAT member for script queries — so
# after a runtime swap, m_model was stale and queries would return
# data from the empty initial model. The s197 m2 structural fix
# drops m_model storage entirely; current_model() reads the live
# model back from Gtk::DropDown::get_model() on every query. This
# test proves the live read works: the "All" sentinel is the row
# rebuild_palette_dropdown unconditionally seeds at index 0, so a
# `text == "All"` assertion only passes if the substrate is seeing
# the post-swap model.
#
# Side effects: the dropdowns are walked through their entries and
# restored to selected == 0 (the launch default — "All" sentinel,
# set by rebuild_palette_dropdown's set_selected(0) call). No
# palette is selected mid-test for an extended period.
#
# Test protocol:
#   1. Open the Scripter window with a project that has at least one
#      swatch library wired (the default new-document template ships
#      one — should be true at any time the Scripter is reachable).
#   2. Load this script.
#   3. Run. Every line should PASS.

#[sub] Fill palette dropdown — "All" sentinel wins at index 0 (post-swap model live).

assert pop_tb_fill_pdd selected == 0
assert pop_tb_fill_pdd text == "All"

#[sub] Stroke palette dropdown — same default state, independent slot.

assert pop_tb_strk_pdd selected == 0
assert pop_tb_strk_pdd text == "All"

#[sub] Fill palette dropdown — pick "All" by name (no-op restoration, but exercises the pick verb).

pop_tb_fill_pdd pick "All"
assert pop_tb_fill_pdd selected == 0
assert pop_tb_fill_pdd text == "All"

#[sub] Stroke palette dropdown — pick "All" by name.

pop_tb_strk_pdd pick "All"
assert pop_tb_strk_pdd selected == 0
assert pop_tb_strk_pdd text == "All"

#[sub] Fill palette dropdown — display the count (palette-library-dependent, just `get`).

get pop_tb_fill_pdd count

#[sub] Stroke palette dropdown — display the count.

get pop_tb_strk_pdd count

#[sub] Done. 2 new substrate widgets, both addressable; structural model-read verified.
